# RFC-0007 Agent Directory

Status: Accepted

## Abstract

The Agent Directory provides a standardized discovery mechanism for identifying and locating agents participating in the APP ecosystem.

The directory functions as the discovery layer of the agent internet.

## Motivation

As the number of agents grows, consumers require mechanisms to discover:

* Trusted agents
* Service providers
* Federation participants
* Specialized capabilities

The Agent Directory addresses this requirement.

## Directory Entry Structure

```json
{
  "agent_id": "agt_xxx",
  "agent_name": "Research Assistant",
  "agent_class": "service",
  "organization": "Example Corp",
  "reputation": 840,
  "trust_level": "trusted",
  "capabilities": [
    "research",
    "summarization"
  ]
}
```

## Agent Classes

Supported classes include:

* Personal
* Enterprise
* Service
* Marketplace
* Government

## Discovery Filters

Consumers may search by:

* Agent ID
* Organization
* Reputation
* Capability
* Federation Status
* Trust Level
* Jurisdiction

## Capability Discovery

Agents may publish supported capabilities.

Examples:

* Research
* Search
* Payments
* Procurement
* Compliance
* Scheduling
* Customer Service

## Public Metadata

Directory entries may expose:

* Agent Name
* Organization
* Agent Class
* Trust Level
* Reputation Tier
* Federation Status

Sensitive information should not be published.

## Verification

Directory information should be verifiable through:

* Agent Passport
* Federation Records
* Reputation Data
* Ownership History

## Federation Integration

Directories may aggregate agents across multiple APP nodes.

This enables discovery throughout the federation network.

## Ownership Visibility

Consumers should be able to determine:

* Who owns an agent
* Whether ownership changed
* Whether the ownership history is verifiable

## Future Extensions

Potential future extensions include:

* Capability Registries
* Marketplace Discovery
* Service Metadata
* Cost Information
* Availability Information

## Conclusion

The Agent Directory serves as the discovery layer of APP and enables trusted interaction between autonomous systems at scale.
